-- Russian Equity Movers: Raspadskaya, Acron, Lukoil, Rosneft
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 2012-01-13T11:11:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/russian-equity-movers-raspadskaya-acron-lukoil-rosneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex (MICEX)  index climbed 0.1
percent to 1,466.62 as of 2:40 p.m. in Moscow, snapping two days
of losses. The dollar-denominated RTS index fell 0.2 percent to
1,454.75.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  OAO Acron (AKRN)  (AKRN RX) fell as much as 2.1 percent, its
biggest intraday drop since Jan. 4, before trading down 0.8
percent at 1,343 rubles. The Russian fertilizer producer offered
to buy back stock from investors that oppose a share
cancellation as part of its reorganization at almost 16 percent
less than yesterday’s closing price in Moscow.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP)  (RASP RX) headed for its strongest close
since September, adding 4.2 percent to 110.56 rubles. The coal
producer is due to report fourth-quarter and full-year
production results today.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN)  ,  Russia ’s biggest oil producer, fell
0.7 percent to 224.56 rubles. At $99.31 a barrel crude was
trading 3.2 percent lower than at the 6:45 p.m. stock market
close in Moscow yesterday.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH)  (LKOH RX), the second-
largest producer, fell 0.3 percent to 1,757.60 rubles. The
company said oil and gas output fell last year as crude
production dropped about 5.5 percent on the decline of western
Siberian fields.  To contact the reporter on this story:
